Package: neon-drm
Version: 1.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: python3, curl, unzip
Recommends: systemd, policykit-1
Maintainer: Nicholas Raimbault <nicholasraimbault@users.noreply.github.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/nicholasraimbault/neon
Description: Fix DRM playback in Chromium-based browsers on Linux
 Neon patches WidevineCdm into browsers that ship without it,
 enabling Netflix, Spotify, Disney+, and other DRM-protected content.
 Supports Helium, Thorium, ungoogled-chromium, and Chromium.
